https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0-S5a0eXPoc

1. expo-cli package:
npm i -g expo-cli

2. needed vscode plugin
 - react native tools
 - React-Native/React/Redux snippets for es6/es7 => generate code really fast.
 - Prettier - Code formatter => beautify our code. press ctrl+S to format out code.

3. Setting up the react native by expo
 - expo init DoneWithIt
 - choose blank + TypeScript

4. folder structure
asset: put media

5. To start
using simulator: npm start
using expo: expo start

5. Running to project and show it on phone via tunnel
 - npm start
 - Switch to the hosting port
 - Choose tunnel mode, and use the phone to scan the QRCODE
 - The Expo client on the mobile phone will be called to build the app

6. To share the app
 - push the project to github
 - https://github.com/avan106206/ReactNativeExpoTomChan
 - browse https://snack.expo.io/ and import the project from github
 - set the branch name and the folder than you can import

7. Install native base
https://docs.nativebase.io/docs/GetStarted.html


 - npm install -save @types/react-native-cli, install react native cli
 - npm install -save native-base, install native base
 - react-native link, to bind the dependency

8. Install okta library

We use okta as the authetication server, take reference for https://developer.okta.com/blog/2019/11/14/react-native-login
https://youtu.be/mkT_I5tm3Ig - youtube

Download okta library
 - npm install --save @okta/okta-react
 
Install oktadev schematics
 - npm install -D @types/@angular-devkit
 - npm i -D @angular/material @angular/cdk @angular/animations

Then run add auth
 - schematics @oktadev/schematics:add-auth

 https://dev-1589119.okta.com/oauth2/default - URL
 0oajruduGcB8Texfh5d5 - ID


9. Prepare Redux
 - npm i -save @types/redux@latest
 - npm i -save @types/react-redux@latest
 - npm i -save @types/redux-thunk@latest
 - npm install --save react-redux
 - npm install --save redux
 - npm install --save redux-thunk